DEPENDENCIES
----------
* Python
* Numpy
  sudo apt-get install python-numpy

* wxPython
* ReportLab
* SimpleJSON


INSTALLING ON OSX
-----------------

homebrew: issues compiling wxpython. Cannot be solved easily.

macports: issue with py2app. Can be solved by installing macports from
source in alternate prefix.


Installing Macport from sources
-------------------------------
Reason: issue with py2app:
http://stackoverflow.com/questions/13131024/py2app-error-for-opencv-macports-app-how-to-compile-opencv-with-headerpad-max-i

Download macport source from https://distfiles.macports.org/MacPorts/
expand archive, and do:
./configure --prefix=/opt/localdepth/localdepth/localdepth/localdepth/local && make && sudo make install

Adjust your PATH have $prefix/bin, $prefix/sbin, and MANPATH to have $prefix/share/man


Installing Python 2.7
---------------------
sudo port install python27
sudo port select --set python python27


Installing needed stuff using Macport
-------------------------------------
sudo port install py27-wxpython-3.0 py27-numpy py27-pil py27-reportlab


Building the app using py2app
-----------------------------
sudo port install py27-py2app

./build_osx.sh